512 Woolwich Street features two single story office buildings situated on 2.11 acres just outside of downtown Guelph’s Exhibition Park neighborhood. Building A (19,920 SF) fronting on Woolwich will be vacated in December and Building B (10,023 SF) has a long term lease in place providing tremendous opportunity for both users and investors. Permitted uses include ; Medical Clinic, Medical Office, Office and more. With over 120 parking stalls, the site offers a generous 4.2 : 1,000 ratio. The site is adjacent to a City of Guelph parkland trail linking to the Downtown Trail. 512 Woolwich Street offers access, amenities and opportunity.

Beautiful three-story mixed use building for sale in the heart of downtown London. Located on the south-west corner of the signalized intersection of Dundas Street and Clarence Street, 215 Dundas Street offers purchasers the opportunity to own a recognizable building with both retail and office potential. Desirable brick and beam aesthetic is possible on the second and third floor office spaces, including approx. 15 ft. ceilings on the third floor with exposed brick. Ground floor retail units leased to local restaurant and Canadian owned cannabis boutique

Fully leased office building available for sale in Downtown London. Located at the northwest corner of Dundas Street and Clarence Street, in the heart of the London's Dundas Place Flex Street. The location provides a wide range of experiences including shops and restaurants, with quick access to Public Transit. 210 Dundas Street is fully leased to a single tenant with a long remaining lease term. This 44,499 SF (including lower level) building offers an appealing mirrored glass facade, and well appointed office space. The current building layout allows for potential conversion to a multi-tenant building in the future if desired. The Building offers 9 underground parking spaces utilized by the current Tenant with additional street parking available in the area.

5,350 Sq. Ft. 3-storey office building on 0.105 acres for sale near the busy intersection of Richmond Street and Oxford Street East. Building being sold vacant. Exposure to over 28,000 vehicles per day. Pylon signage. Excellent visibility and exposure. Walking distance to Richmond Row and the downtown core. Space is divided into the following: Main floor 1,750 Sq. Ft.; 2nd floor 1,750 Sq. Ft.; 3rd floor 850 Sq. Ft.; finished lower level with windows: 1,000 Sq. Ft. 7 on-site shared parking spaces. Building is ideal for either one user or multiple tenants. Also available for lease - see MLS #s 40116585, 40116581, 40116285.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Totally renovated and updated house with the charm of a century home built circa 1890. High ceilings, stained glass, some original main floor hardwood flooring combined with a modern kitchen featuring high end appliances and island seating. Main floor powder room near the side entrance. There are 4 bedrooms on the 2nd level with 2nd floor laundry. Great opportunity for a home based business with high street exposure or make the conversion entirely to a business. There is a large rear deck and a fully fenced and landscaped yard that is very private. Roof, furnace, windows, awnings and insulation have all recently been updated. Too many updates to mention, and pride of ownership is evident. Close to many amenities in the heart of Lambeth and close to Highway 402 and Highway 401.
